# Frontend Environment Variables Template

# ==============================================================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (when running 'npm start' or 'npm run build' on your host)
# ==============================================================================
# Backend API URL - Used at build time and in development server
# This is ONLY relevant when developing locally on your machine
# REACT_APP_API_URL=http://your-backend-host:5000

# ==============================================================================
# DOCKER CONTAINER DEPLOYMENT
# ==============================================================================
# These variables are used by the nginx reverse-proxy inside the container
# Set them via docker-compose.yml or 'docker run --env' flags

# Backend host address (when running in container)
# Defaults to: host.docker.internal (Docker Desktop for Windows/Mac)
# For Docker on Linux, use the host gateway IP or container service name
# BACKEND_HOST=backend  # or host.docker.internal or 192.168.1.100

# Backend port (when running in container)
# Defaults to: 5000
# BACKEND_PORT=5000

# ==============================================================================
# USAGE EXAMPLES
# ==============================================================================

# 1. Local npm development (on host machine):
#    $ REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000 npm start

# 2. Docker with docker-compose:
#    Uses BACKEND_HOST and BACKEND_PORT from docker-compose.yml environment section
#    $ docker-compose up

# 3. Docker with docker run:
#    $ docker run -p 80:80 \
#      -e BACKEND_HOST=host.docker.internal \
#      -e BACKEND_PORT=5000 \
#      your-frontend-image

# 4. Cross-machine development:
#    $ docker run -p 80:80 \
#      -e BACKEND_HOST=192.168.1.100 \
#      -e BACKEND_PORT=5000 \
#      your-frontend-image

